#Type casting is the process of converting a variable from one data type to another. In Python, you can use built-in functions like int(), float(), str(), etc., to perform type casting.
example of type casting:
int("123") # converts the string "123" to the integer 123
float("3.14") # converts the string "3.14" to the float 3.14
str(456) # converts the integer 456 to the string "456"     

    

